id: pm-x26a
title: "GH-488: path-target pm init emits executable tracker-scoped follow-up commands"
description: Path-like pm init targets must emit follow-up and recovery commands that resolve the initialized tracker instead of assuming workspace discovery.
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[5]: agent-experience,gh-issue,init,path-safety,token-efficiency
created_at: "2026-07-10T04:24:54.193Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-10T08:05:07.959Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-10T08:05:06.550Z"
author: codex-root-20260709
estimated_minutes: 120
acceptance_criteria: Path-target init output and recovery bundles render executable --pm-path-scoped follow-ups; workspace-target mode creates <dir>/.agents/pm without changing legacy tracker-root semantics; SDK result contracts expose resolved target semantics; integration tests execute every emitted next step; docs and contracts remain aligned.
parent: pm-mpbb
risk: medium
confidence: high
severity: medium
environment: @unbrained/pm-cli 2026.7.9 path-target initialization
repro_steps: "Initialize a temporary path with pm init <path> --defaults, cd into that path, then run the emitted bare pm create/context commands; discovery incorrectly checks <path>/.agents/pm."
resolution: Added explicit workspace/tracker target contracts and tracker-scoped executable init follow-ups.
expected_result: Path-target and workspace-target init output resolves the initialized tracker for every follow-up.
actual_result: All emitted pm commands are scoped when discovery is unavailable; integration and packed proof pass.
