comments[5]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-10T04:24:54.193Z",codex-root-20260709,"Duplicate check: searched all statuses for GH-488, path-target init follow-up commands, initialized tracker next steps, and prior path-target fixes. No item owns executable post-init guidance; closed pm-jek2 covers caller-settings corruption only."
  "2026-07-10T05:53:24.372Z",codex-root-20260709,"Verification evidence 2026-07-10: full sandbox suite passed 270 files / 5,505 tests with exact 100% statements, branches, functions, and lines. pm test-all over the seven active items passed 8 linked commands with 0 failures and 1 duplicate-safe skip. pnpm typecheck, contracts:check, lint (ESLint + 0 jscpd clones + static quality/token budget), docs-skills, context-eval, security scan, and audit all passed. Live CodeFactor reports A+ and 0 issues. Fresh packed npm install at /tmp/pm-cli-sdk-path-proof-XIsSsh activated 11 bundled packages in a path-target tracker, left caller extension files at zero, and passed CLI/SDK context plus isolated doctor with zero blocking failures. pm health is clean and history drift is zero."
  "2026-07-10T06:23:45.590Z",codex-root-20260709,"Greptile pre-push review 388e369e found and we fixed replacement-string expansion in scoped agent-guidance commands by using a replacement callback. A regression covers tracker paths containing the special $& sequence. Focused 149 tests, full 5,505-test exact 100/100/100/100 coverage, typecheck, contracts, lint, static quality, and zero-clone gates pass after the fix."
  "2026-07-10T06:38:36.124Z",codex-root-20260709,"PR #491 CodeQL evidence: alert 16 identified an incomplete single-occurrence dollar escape in the replacement-sensitive-path test expectation. The regression now uses replaceAll and a path containing three dollar characters, so it proves every shell-sensitive occurrence is escaped. Focused init tests, typecheck, ESLint, zero-clone jscpd, static-quality, docstring, and token-budget gates pass."
  "2026-07-10T08:05:02.504Z",codex-root-20260709,"Fresh PR #491 P1 closeout: the workspace-root safety guard now keys off resolved tracker-target mode, covering both a path-like positional and --pm-path. Packed install proof at /tmp/pm-pr491-packed-OkUpBn returned usage exit 2/code workspace_root_pm_path for positional repository-root init, while explicit --workspace initialized project/.agents/pm successfully. Exact coverage and linked tests pass."
